WEBVTT

00:07.311 --> 00:10.271
[insects chirping]

00:32.423 --> 00:35.252
[ominous music]

00:35.383 --> 00:39.039
♪

00:39.169 --> 00:41.998
- [breathing heavily]

00:51.181 --> 00:54.097
[device beeping]

00:54.228 --> 00:58.797
♪

00:58.928 --> 01:01.191
- Chill!
- [gasps]

01:01.322 --> 01:03.106
- Come back!

01:03.237 --> 01:10.070
♪

01:12.507 --> 01:13.856
[grunts]
- Let me go!

01:13.986 --> 01:15.945
- Shh. Shh.

01:16.076 --> 01:19.079
Calm. Calm your craze.

01:19.209 --> 01:20.950
Give me what's in your hand.
- You can't have it.

01:25.694 --> 01:27.174
[device beeps]

01:28.697 --> 01:29.959
You're making a mistake.

01:30.090 --> 01:33.354
- It's too late for this.
- No.

01:33.484 --> 01:34.964
It's not too late.

01:37.009 --> 01:39.099
- I'm doing this for you,
can't you see?

01:42.232 --> 01:43.712
- Just let go.

01:45.540 --> 01:47.542
- For all of us.

01:47.672 --> 01:50.458
For our future.

01:50.588 --> 01:52.155
- [inhales shakily]
No.

01:52.286 --> 01:58.030
♪

01:58.161 --> 02:00.207
- Chill! Stop!

02:01.991 --> 02:04.211
[both grunting]

02:05.603 --> 02:08.432
[birds chirping]

02:10.086 --> 02:12.262
- Everything's changing.

02:12.393 --> 02:15.700
- So that's good.
You need to get unstuck.

02:15.831 --> 02:17.789
- Maybe I like being stuck.
- [chuckles]

02:19.356 --> 02:21.532
Have you talked to her
about how you feel?

02:21.663 --> 02:24.361
- I've tried.
She doesn't want to.

02:24.492 --> 02:27.059
We're "past talking," I guess.
- Mm.

02:27.190 --> 02:28.235
- She used to look me
in the eye.

02:28.365 --> 02:29.410
- Mm-hmm.
- We'd see each other.

02:29.540 --> 02:30.802
- The sizzle.

02:30.933 --> 02:31.977
- We'd feel it.
- Yeah.

02:32.108 --> 02:33.501
- I miss it.
- Mm.

02:33.631 --> 02:35.459
What about Fritz the Fireman?

02:37.374 --> 02:40.160
- Well, he's coming around
the house a lot.

02:40.290 --> 02:42.336
Kids are getting used to him.

02:42.466 --> 02:44.903
I'm not a fool.
- Oh, no. You are a fool, Paul.

02:45.034 --> 02:47.558
That's been long established.

02:47.689 --> 02:49.908
- They drift away, Arlo.

02:50.039 --> 02:51.519
That's what happens.
- And you watch and do nothing.

02:51.649 --> 02:52.998
- Not true.

02:53.129 --> 02:54.870
I think and think and think.

02:55.000 --> 02:57.046
Got so many thinks,
I can't sleep.

02:59.657 --> 03:02.312
- I have a way out
when I can't sleep now.

03:02.443 --> 03:03.835
- What's your trick?

03:05.924 --> 03:08.579
- I get up, I go outside,
I get naked in the dark.

03:08.710 --> 03:09.798
- [chuckles]
- Stop.

03:09.928 --> 03:12.192
I put my bare feet in the dirt.

03:12.322 --> 03:16.674
I'm small under trees,
stars, sky.

03:18.328 --> 03:19.938
Big problems
don't find small men.

03:20.069 --> 03:21.853
- Hmm. Get small.

03:21.984 --> 03:23.290
- Get small.

03:23.420 --> 03:26.293
[ominous music]

03:26.423 --> 03:33.343
♪

03:37.956 --> 03:39.219
Hmm.

03:42.134 --> 03:43.223
- Who is she?

03:46.356 --> 03:49.098
[device whirs, chimes]

03:49.229 --> 03:53.058
- Victim: Chill Spen.

03:53.189 --> 03:56.453
Body's cool, 92 degrees.

03:56.584 --> 03:57.585
How long's she been dead,
Detective Arlo?

03:57.715 --> 03:58.890
Do the math.

04:00.370 --> 04:01.589
- Four hours?

04:05.027 --> 04:06.855
- You're a bad detective.
- [scoffs]

04:06.985 --> 04:09.074
- She's dead seven hours,
and a half.

04:09.205 --> 04:10.467
- Oh, who cares?

04:10.598 --> 04:12.164
Chancellor does it all for you.

04:12.295 --> 04:14.297
You think
you're Sherlock Hones.

04:14.428 --> 04:15.951
- Holmes.

04:18.432 --> 04:22.305
What her soul saw.
- What her soul saw.

04:22.436 --> 04:23.437
- Must have been
grizzle and anguish

04:23.567 --> 04:24.960
as she flew to air.

04:26.788 --> 04:29.181
Why were you wandering
the dark, deep woods

04:29.312 --> 04:30.661
at night, lady?

04:30.792 --> 04:34.622
- Who killed Chill Spen?
The mystery begins.

04:36.188 --> 04:39.279
[device chimes, whirs]

04:39.409 --> 04:40.758
- Strego Nall is the killer.

04:40.889 --> 04:43.152
- The mystery ends.

04:44.501 --> 04:46.286
Where's Nall now?

04:46.416 --> 04:48.810
- Strego Nall's in Back Park,
around Middle Way.

04:48.940 --> 04:51.029
- Mm. Case closed, Sherlock.

04:51.160 --> 04:52.814
I'll tell them to round him up.

04:52.944 --> 04:54.076
- [gasps]

04:56.296 --> 04:57.949
Hello.

04:58.080 --> 05:00.212
Who are you?

05:00.343 --> 05:02.084
We are police.

05:03.303 --> 05:04.652
- Asus.

05:06.567 --> 05:07.829
- Did you see the killing?

05:09.483 --> 05:10.658
- Nay.

05:15.402 --> 05:18.840
- The victim, did she reach out
to you for help?

05:20.320 --> 05:21.495
- No.

05:25.499 --> 05:28.458
The dreadfeel swept through me.

05:28.589 --> 05:30.765
[soft dramatic music]

05:30.895 --> 05:33.507
I felt trouble.

05:33.637 --> 05:35.291
Searched the glade.

05:37.728 --> 05:39.295
I came here.

05:40.949 --> 05:42.733
But too late.

05:42.864 --> 05:45.170
- You had the dreadfeel?

05:45.301 --> 05:46.868
So you know the dead.

05:48.565 --> 05:50.001
- My sister.

05:52.830 --> 05:54.310
- Sorry, sister.

05:56.486 --> 05:59.794
Sister Asus,
since we are detectives,

05:59.924 --> 06:01.622
we lug the Bright.

06:04.146 --> 06:05.669
Will you take it?

06:05.800 --> 06:08.063
It will release you
from memory, pain, and drudge.

06:08.193 --> 06:09.456
You can take it now.
Here and done.

06:09.586 --> 06:11.893
- No. No Bright.

06:12.023 --> 06:13.634
- Are you sure?
- I don't want it.

06:13.764 --> 06:18.290
♪

06:18.421 --> 06:21.293
- I'm Paul Sarno.

06:21.424 --> 06:24.296
You reach me
if you change your mind.

06:25.646 --> 06:27.648
I will see your sister
cared for and justiced.

06:30.215 --> 06:31.608
- Grats.

06:31.739 --> 06:38.572
♪

06:57.895 --> 07:00.681
[dramatic music]

07:00.811 --> 07:07.601
♪

07:47.292 --> 07:49.599
- The clock ticks down.

07:49.730 --> 07:52.210
After more than 100 years
of preparations,

07:52.341 --> 07:55.300
only two weeks remain
before the Bridge,

07:55.431 --> 07:57.564
our way forward
to a better future,

07:57.694 --> 07:59.870
is set to begin
with the arrival on Earth

08:00.001 --> 08:02.743
of the First Wave of Lunars.

08:02.873 --> 08:05.485
And Earth is eager
for what they bring--

08:05.615 --> 08:08.705
planet-saving advances
created by IO,

08:08.836 --> 08:11.186
humanity's self-teaching
artificial intelligence

08:11.316 --> 08:13.710
buried in the Moon.

08:13.841 --> 08:16.147
Indira Mare,
known to most of the world

08:16.278 --> 08:17.932
as the Envoy of IO,

08:18.062 --> 08:20.021
reiterated her trust
in IO's ability

08:20.151 --> 08:21.936
to deliver tested solutions

08:22.066 --> 08:24.155
to our
most daunting challenges.

08:24.286 --> 08:27.332
- The technology
to save our world is coming,

08:27.463 --> 08:29.813
and so are the people

08:29.944 --> 08:32.773
who can teach us how to live
in harmony with this power

08:32.903 --> 08:35.297
and each other.

08:35.427 --> 08:37.168
What's happening up there,

08:37.299 --> 08:39.954
this isn't simply about
solving the crushing problems

08:40.084 --> 08:41.869
of our planet.

08:41.999 --> 08:44.436
It's about solving us.

08:44.567 --> 08:47.265
[sweeping music]

08:47.396 --> 08:50.312
[rain pattering]

08:54.098 --> 08:55.709
- [exhales]

09:02.890 --> 09:05.632
[soft dramatic music]

09:05.762 --> 09:12.682
♪

09:16.338 --> 09:18.253
[monitor chimes]

09:30.221 --> 09:34.965
♪

09:35.096 --> 09:38.055
[beeping]

09:48.936 --> 09:50.154
[beeps]

09:50.285 --> 09:51.852
- Bella Sway,
transport logistics.

09:51.982 --> 09:53.418
Flight priority.

09:53.549 --> 09:55.682
- You're the first loop
out of here in a month.

09:55.812 --> 09:57.684
- You'll miss the quiet
soon enough.

10:05.996 --> 10:08.695
[faint classical music
playing]

10:08.825 --> 10:12.612
♪

10:12.742 --> 10:13.961
[door clicks]

10:14.091 --> 10:20.968
♪

10:25.320 --> 10:26.713
- You are?

10:28.584 --> 10:30.934
- Pilot. You?

10:32.109 --> 10:33.328
- Muscle.

10:34.938 --> 10:36.200
- This is scheduled
to be a cargo flight.

10:36.331 --> 10:38.420
I wasn't expecting passengers.

10:38.550 --> 10:40.901
- We weren't expecting
to fly with you.

10:41.031 --> 10:43.947
We usually keep to ourselves,
but...

10:44.078 --> 10:45.732
our pilot is sick.

10:45.862 --> 10:47.516
Plans change.

10:51.085 --> 10:51.999
- Who's "we"?

10:53.696 --> 10:55.437
- You're Bella.

10:58.092 --> 11:01.051
Our names hold our story.
Did you know that?

11:01.182 --> 11:02.705
My mother taught me that.

11:02.836 --> 11:03.750
Here.

11:06.100 --> 11:08.189
I...am Tomm.

11:08.319 --> 11:09.799
- Tomm.

11:09.930 --> 11:12.759
I don't think I asked you
to explain anything to me.

11:15.109 --> 11:16.327
- I am Tomm.

11:17.807 --> 11:21.028
My destiny will take me
to the mountains.

11:22.377 --> 11:24.858
Which ones? That's the mystery.

11:24.988 --> 11:26.686
But I get the gist.

11:27.948 --> 11:29.863
You are Bella.

11:31.386 --> 11:33.562
- [clears throat]

11:33.693 --> 11:35.259
I was told
it meant "beautiful."

11:35.390 --> 11:37.522
- Oh, it does.

11:37.653 --> 11:40.308
It also means "war."
Did you know that?

11:40.438 --> 11:43.703
Now, are you beauty
or are you war?

11:43.833 --> 11:45.705
- Why make me choose?
[crunches]

11:49.926 --> 11:52.450
- I see...

11:52.581 --> 11:54.539
"Be all."

11:55.758 --> 11:57.717
Maybe that's God.

11:59.153 --> 12:01.329
I see a bell ringing
with all the noise of life.

12:03.157 --> 12:04.593
I see an A.

12:05.986 --> 12:07.901
It stands alone.

12:09.685 --> 12:11.731
What do you see?

12:14.429 --> 12:16.561
- I see...

12:16.692 --> 12:18.912
that you're
a bad fortune-teller, Tomm.

12:21.915 --> 12:23.873
You said you're muscle.

12:24.004 --> 12:25.875
Who do you protect?

12:27.181 --> 12:28.269
[door clicks]

12:30.314 --> 12:32.752
- Indira, they're waiting
for you in quarantine,

12:32.882 --> 12:35.929
This is Bella, our new pilot.

12:37.887 --> 12:39.715
- Indira Mare.

12:39.846 --> 12:41.673
- Nice to meet you, Bella.

12:41.804 --> 12:43.545
Get us there and back
in one piece, please.

12:43.675 --> 12:45.199
- Sure. Yes.

12:45.329 --> 12:46.722
Good sleep.

12:51.683 --> 12:55.383
[chuckles]
I'm flying the Envoy of IO?

12:55.513 --> 12:57.341
- Don't worry. You were vetted.

12:57.472 --> 12:59.343
Your military experience
qualifies you.

12:59.474 --> 13:01.606
Besides, I'd stake my life
on anyone

13:01.737 --> 13:03.434
who's survived
what you survived.

13:03.565 --> 13:05.132
- I'm not what I was.

13:06.611 --> 13:08.570
- No one escapes
where they've been.

13:10.702 --> 13:12.095
See you on the Moon.

13:14.271 --> 13:15.707
- Shit.

13:15.838 --> 13:18.710
[dramatic music]

13:18.841 --> 13:25.761
♪

13:29.373 --> 13:32.246
[rapid beeping]

13:36.163 --> 13:38.295
You could have told me
who my passenger was,

13:38.426 --> 13:40.036
and her bodyguard.

13:40.167 --> 13:42.169
Might be
a little extra scrutiny, no?

13:42.299 --> 13:44.301
Having Indira Mare on board?

13:44.432 --> 13:46.042
- Hey, hey, how do you think
we got your launch slot

13:46.173 --> 13:48.088
moved up by six weeks, huh?

13:48.218 --> 13:49.393
This is a gift.

13:49.524 --> 13:51.265
- What's the job?

13:51.395 --> 13:54.311
- We want you to bring us home
a Singer.

13:54.442 --> 13:57.271
It's their name for a drug,
a mechano-pharmasude.

13:57.401 --> 13:59.055
It's used in one
of their kook ceremonies.

13:59.186 --> 14:00.448
They say it uses nanos

14:00.578 --> 14:01.971
to blow open
the doors of perception

14:02.102 --> 14:04.234
to your inner life
or some such shit.

14:04.365 --> 14:05.583
Anyway,
nothing like it down here.

14:05.714 --> 14:07.063
- Not yet.

14:07.194 --> 14:09.196
They're coming for you, Jatey.

14:09.326 --> 14:10.850
- You know, if anyone
should take a good look

14:10.980 --> 14:12.721
at their inner life,
that'd be you, Bella.

14:12.852 --> 14:14.941
- I can't think
of a worse high.

14:15.071 --> 14:16.899
- One sample's all we need
to dupe it here.

14:17.030 --> 14:19.815
All you gotta do
is park and wait.

14:19.946 --> 14:20.947
They'll deliver it to you.

14:21.077 --> 14:22.600
- [sighs]

14:22.731 --> 14:29.694
♪

14:30.870 --> 14:32.219
[beeping]

14:32.349 --> 14:34.351
[door whirs]

14:51.020 --> 14:54.502
- The great and powerful
Envoy of IO.

14:58.375 --> 14:59.681
Honk.

15:02.858 --> 15:09.734
♪

15:12.520 --> 15:15.392
[monitor beeping]

15:22.486 --> 15:25.707
[insects chirping]

15:25.837 --> 15:28.623
[indistinct chatter]

15:35.195 --> 15:37.066
- Hello, Sarno. Noon.

15:37.197 --> 15:38.676
- We've come to checkbox
the Chill Spen killer.

15:38.807 --> 15:40.461
- Strego Nall?
- You checked him in?

15:40.591 --> 15:42.028
- Cell 3.

15:44.160 --> 15:46.989
[tense music]

15:47.120 --> 15:49.949
♪

15:50.079 --> 15:51.820
- Wake cell.
[machine chimes]

15:53.256 --> 15:54.649
- Strego Nall.

15:56.216 --> 15:58.435
Do you admit
to killing Chill Spen?

16:00.263 --> 16:01.656
- Does it matter?

16:01.786 --> 16:05.877
[device whirs, chimes]

16:06.008 --> 16:12.972
♪

16:17.367 --> 16:19.587
- The Moon is no place
for the dark you bring.

16:22.459 --> 16:23.895
Guilty.

16:24.026 --> 16:25.332
[device beeps]

16:27.160 --> 16:28.335
Lunch.

16:35.037 --> 16:36.778
- I know
you'll make this right.

16:38.998 --> 16:41.000
You'll heal
what you've wounded.

16:43.176 --> 16:45.178
- I don't deserve to be healed.

16:48.268 --> 16:49.704
[both grunt]

16:49.834 --> 16:52.098
- [breathing heavily]

16:52.228 --> 16:55.014
♪

16:55.144 --> 16:57.146
Okay. Okay.
[grunts]

17:00.106 --> 17:01.498
- You want us to go after?

17:01.629 --> 17:03.457
- No. Where's he gonna go?

17:03.587 --> 17:05.415
We'll find him.

17:05.546 --> 17:07.635
I got something else for you.

17:09.071 --> 17:10.333
- Come on.

17:12.727 --> 17:14.033
[ship whirring]

17:14.163 --> 17:16.861
- Wake up.
We're coming in.

17:16.992 --> 17:20.387
You can take off the nose pin.
Drink as much as you can.

17:20.517 --> 17:22.911
- [exhales]

17:34.401 --> 17:36.490
- You needn't worry.
[inhales sharply]

17:36.620 --> 17:40.059
Tomm comes up slowly,
like an old hibernating bear.

17:41.973 --> 17:43.801
Do you make this run often?

17:43.932 --> 17:46.065
- Once or twice a month
with cargo.

17:46.195 --> 17:48.763
But I stay on the ship.
I'm not allowed on Glade.

17:48.893 --> 17:50.634
- They let
very few outsiders in.

17:50.765 --> 17:52.071
- Yeah.

17:52.201 --> 17:54.856
I'm fine with that.

17:54.986 --> 17:57.511
- You never wanted
to see your future?

17:57.641 --> 18:00.209
- I'm glad to hear IO's solved
all of our problems.

18:00.340 --> 18:02.255
Earth could use some easy.

18:02.385 --> 18:04.213
The sooner we get it,
the better.

18:04.344 --> 18:06.302
- IO's only a tool.

18:06.433 --> 18:08.696
It needs people to teach it,
guide it,

18:08.826 --> 18:10.828
so it can guide us.

18:10.959 --> 18:12.395
- Guide us where?

18:14.180 --> 18:15.877
- To the end of suffering.

18:16.007 --> 18:17.922
- [chuckles]

18:19.620 --> 18:20.969
- There's no shortage of people

18:21.100 --> 18:23.102
who wanna disrupt
what we're doing.

18:24.929 --> 18:27.671
But if it works...
- It must work.

18:27.802 --> 18:30.109
[sighs] It will work.

18:31.936 --> 18:34.113
This is Bella.
- Yes.

18:34.243 --> 18:36.115
- Bella stands alone.

18:36.245 --> 18:40.771
- I stand apart,
and I'm fine with that.

18:40.902 --> 18:43.774
- Apart, but not alone.

18:43.905 --> 18:44.993
I like her.

18:47.561 --> 18:49.040
- We're on approach.

18:49.171 --> 18:52.305
You mind some music?
It helps me concentrate.

18:55.438 --> 18:58.354
["Ne Me Quitte Pas" playing]

18:58.485 --> 19:02.358
- [singing in French]

19:02.489 --> 19:04.621
- I didn't take you
for a romantic.

19:07.407 --> 19:08.843
If you don't like it here,
Bella,

19:08.973 --> 19:10.801
why do you keep coming back?

19:10.932 --> 19:12.673
- I like to be miserable,

19:12.803 --> 19:15.589
but apparently,
that's going out of style.

19:15.719 --> 19:17.504
- [chuckles]

19:17.634 --> 19:20.463
♪

19:20.594 --> 19:22.204
[whirring]
- Buckle up.

19:22.335 --> 19:25.076
- [singing in French]

19:25.207 --> 19:32.171
♪

19:34.085 --> 19:36.914
[music heightens]

19:37.045 --> 19:44.008
♪

19:56.238 --> 19:59.067
[music softens]

19:59.198 --> 20:06.074
♪

20:12.428 --> 20:15.301
[ship whirring]

20:15.431 --> 20:17.912
[rumbling]

20:21.568 --> 20:27.878
♪

20:39.803 --> 20:42.110
[ship whooshes]

20:42.241 --> 20:49.117
♪

21:07.614 --> 21:14.534
♪

21:23.543 --> 21:26.154
[door whirs]

21:32.073 --> 21:33.857
- What's the pistol for?

21:33.988 --> 21:35.163
To shoot yourself

21:35.294 --> 21:37.208
if you get
too blissed out here?

21:37.339 --> 21:39.559
- Doesn't work on Glade.
No weapons do.

21:39.689 --> 21:42.257
But I do like what it does
for my silhouette.

21:42.388 --> 21:43.824
- If you'd like to come ashore
with us,

21:43.954 --> 21:45.521
you can be my guest.

21:45.652 --> 21:48.655
It might change your mind.
- I should stay on CAT.

21:48.785 --> 21:50.657
- Dance with the dark, Bella.

21:50.787 --> 21:52.267
- That's what they say here.

21:52.398 --> 21:55.357
- The darkness is a gift
you must embrace.

21:55.488 --> 21:57.141
- Why?

21:57.272 --> 21:59.318
- Because you are the light.

22:09.066 --> 22:12.461
[bird squawking]

22:12.592 --> 22:18.032
- ♪ Welcomin, welcomin

22:18.162 --> 22:23.777
♪ Oh, Mother, oh, Mother

22:23.907 --> 22:30.087
♪ We are your children
[people harmonizing]

22:30.218 --> 22:36.355
♪ We round you, surround you

22:36.485 --> 22:43.057
all: ♪ Let the Moon remember

22:43.187 --> 22:49.585
♪ All that was best before

22:49.716 --> 22:56.026
♪ And light the way forward

22:56.157 --> 23:02.555
- ♪ The future is better

23:04.687 --> 23:06.036
- I wasn't expecting you
to meet me,

23:06.167 --> 23:08.778
Council Chair Maite.

23:08.909 --> 23:10.911
- Why should I hide away?

23:11.041 --> 23:13.261
Make you think me bigger,
better?

23:13.392 --> 23:15.916
[chuckles]
No time for pompfluff.

23:16.046 --> 23:17.613
The future is better.

23:17.744 --> 23:18.919
- Yes.

23:19.049 --> 23:21.878
[children shouting, laughing]

23:22.009 --> 23:24.446
[soft atmospheric music]

23:24.577 --> 23:26.970
I'm always unprepared.

23:27.101 --> 23:28.798
It's beautiful.

23:28.929 --> 23:31.061
- We live and die
by the grace of IO,

23:31.192 --> 23:33.194
and we have you to thank.

23:33.324 --> 23:35.239
- I am only the messenger.

23:36.545 --> 23:38.765
- Nay hide your power, Envoy.

23:38.895 --> 23:40.767
Those who make IO
make the world.

23:42.508 --> 23:44.292
- IO serves the world.

23:44.423 --> 23:46.555
It works for the many.

23:46.686 --> 23:50.385
When IO serves the few,
we'll shut it down.

23:50.516 --> 23:52.387
- We look forward to your
address tomorrow, Envoy.

23:52.518 --> 23:54.868
It means much
that you came here to make it.

23:54.998 --> 23:58.001
- The First Wave is eager
to return to the Mother.

23:58.132 --> 24:01.222
We've waited a long time
for this moment.

24:01.352 --> 24:03.529
- Now the real work begins.

24:03.659 --> 24:07.924
♪

24:08.055 --> 24:10.144
[bird calling]

24:10.274 --> 24:17.151
♪

24:24.201 --> 24:26.987
[pelican squawking]

24:27.117 --> 24:33.994
♪

24:37.171 --> 24:40.000
[object chirping]

24:42.350 --> 24:45.179
[chirping]

25:11.248 --> 25:12.423
- Hmm.

25:12.554 --> 25:15.426
[alarm beeping]

25:15.557 --> 25:18.517
[distant banging]

25:22.172 --> 25:23.565
- Your ship makes a good drum.

25:23.696 --> 25:24.914
[banging]

25:25.045 --> 25:27.264
Paul Sarno. This is Arlo Noon.

25:27.395 --> 25:28.352
We are police.

25:30.485 --> 25:31.878
Can we come in?

25:33.619 --> 25:34.663
[door whirs]

25:48.242 --> 25:49.286
Oh.
- Yeah.

25:49.417 --> 25:51.375
- Yeah. Nice.

25:51.506 --> 25:52.986
[door whirs]

25:53.116 --> 25:55.249
Metals. Yeah.

25:56.903 --> 25:58.731
Oh, composites.
- Ah.

25:58.861 --> 25:59.819
- You know, we have wood,
mostly.

25:59.949 --> 26:02.691
- Mm. Mostly wood.

26:02.822 --> 26:06.565
- So what seems to be
the problem, officers?

26:09.132 --> 26:10.525
- Oh.
- Oh.

26:10.656 --> 26:12.919
[chuckles]
- Yes. Hmm.

26:13.049 --> 26:15.443
Well, I'm afraid there's been
a discovery, ma'am.

26:15.574 --> 26:17.140
- Mm-hmm.

26:17.271 --> 26:18.446
- You need to come downtown
with us to the station.

26:19.621 --> 26:21.318
- Are we playing
Cops and Robbers?

26:21.449 --> 26:22.450
- [laughs]

26:22.581 --> 26:24.408
- Yeah.

26:24.539 --> 26:26.672
That's how they used to do it
in the, uh, good ol' days.

26:26.802 --> 26:28.195
- [laughs]
"Downtown."

26:28.325 --> 26:30.414
[both laugh]
- Yeah. The good ol' days.

26:30.545 --> 26:32.286
Well, I'm not going anywhere.

26:32.416 --> 26:34.418
Bang. Bang.
[blows, clicks tongue]

26:34.549 --> 26:36.638
You're dead. Yeehaw.

26:36.769 --> 26:37.726
- Yeehaw!

26:37.857 --> 26:39.510
[laughter]

26:39.641 --> 26:41.991
- Yeah. Yeehaw.

26:42.122 --> 26:44.733
You, um, do need
to come with us, though.

26:49.346 --> 26:51.348
- The Envoy won't be happy
about this.

26:51.479 --> 26:53.307
I'm her pilot.

26:53.437 --> 26:55.657
- You can send word
if you like.

26:55.788 --> 26:57.703
- Have I been charged
with anything?

26:59.530 --> 27:01.097
Can I get a lawyer?

27:01.228 --> 27:02.795
- We have no lawyers here.

27:02.925 --> 27:05.493
That is why this is a utopia.

27:05.624 --> 27:07.713
[indistinct shouting]

27:07.843 --> 27:10.324
[drum and violin music playing]

27:10.454 --> 27:12.805
all: [chanting] Hoe-tee-ta!

27:12.935 --> 27:15.895
Hee! Hoe-tee-ta!

27:16.025 --> 27:17.984
- The Kinetobet.

27:18.114 --> 27:20.290
Dance alphabet.
We all learn it.

27:20.421 --> 27:21.552
♪

27:21.683 --> 27:22.815
all: Toe!

27:24.033 --> 27:25.295
Ha!

27:25.426 --> 27:27.907
Hoe-tee-ta!

27:28.037 --> 27:29.169
Tee!

27:29.299 --> 27:32.781
♪

27:32.912 --> 27:35.654
[both breathing deeply]

27:45.489 --> 27:47.622
- Two breaths
to clear the mind.

27:47.753 --> 27:50.016
It's our custom.
Would you like to try?

27:50.146 --> 27:51.800
- No.

27:51.931 --> 27:53.759
You still haven't told me
why I'm here.

27:53.889 --> 27:55.325
- Why did you come to the Moon?

27:55.456 --> 27:57.153
- I'm a pilot. It's my job.

27:57.284 --> 27:58.807
- You like to fly?

27:58.938 --> 28:00.548
- The money's good.

28:00.679 --> 28:02.332
- Mm. You like money?

28:02.463 --> 28:04.204
- Seriously?

28:04.334 --> 28:06.162
- We have no money here.

28:07.860 --> 28:10.036
- Where was your mind
yesterday night?

28:10.166 --> 28:11.994
- Uh...

28:12.125 --> 28:15.345
it was about 45,000 miles
away from here.

28:16.651 --> 28:18.914
Look, if this is about
the encrypted call to Earth,

28:19.045 --> 28:21.308
I was testing
my secondary comm channels.

28:21.438 --> 28:23.310
It's routine.
I can show you records.

28:23.440 --> 28:27.009
- No. This is not about a call.

28:27.140 --> 28:28.707
It's about murder.

28:30.447 --> 28:32.711
And you've felt nothing
since yesterday?

28:32.841 --> 28:35.104
- Why do you keep asking me
what I feel?

28:35.235 --> 28:37.846
- Here we acknowledge
the dreadfeel.

28:37.977 --> 28:40.109
When your heart sees
a dying person's fright-scream,

28:40.240 --> 28:42.938
you feel troubled, here.

28:43.069 --> 28:44.418
It's usually someone you love.

28:45.898 --> 28:47.943
- I had nothing to do
with any murder.

28:48.074 --> 28:49.379
I didn't even know
you had murders here.

28:49.510 --> 28:51.381
I thought this was paradise.

28:51.512 --> 28:53.079
- Snakes still slither.

28:54.645 --> 28:57.213
- Tell us about your mada.

28:57.344 --> 28:59.781
- My...
- Your mother.

28:59.912 --> 29:01.696
She was a Mooner, right?

29:01.827 --> 29:02.915
One of us?

29:04.568 --> 29:06.614
- I never knew my mother.

29:09.225 --> 29:14.230
I heard she decided
to come here after I was born.

29:14.361 --> 29:16.189
She left me behind.

29:16.319 --> 29:18.321
Didn't want the company,
I guess.

29:18.452 --> 29:20.019
- All your trips here,

29:20.149 --> 29:22.761
you've never had
the yearn to reconnect?

29:22.891 --> 29:24.458
- The yearn?

29:24.588 --> 29:26.112
- We all want connection.

29:26.242 --> 29:27.461
- Do we?

29:30.159 --> 29:33.206
Uh, look, if she's done
something wrong up here,

29:33.336 --> 29:36.470
I am the last person
who would care about that.

29:36.600 --> 29:38.559
She gave me up,
so I gave her up.

29:38.689 --> 29:40.039
[chuckles]

29:40.169 --> 29:44.217
And if you wanna know
how I feel about that...

29:44.347 --> 29:46.088
I feel nothing.

29:49.048 --> 29:51.485
I'm done with this.

29:51.615 --> 29:53.008
- Your sister is dead.

29:53.139 --> 29:55.010
- I don't have a sister.

29:55.141 --> 29:57.012
- Her name is Chill Spen.

29:57.143 --> 29:59.058
She's six years younger.

29:59.188 --> 30:01.974
- The gonesoul was found
this morning.

30:02.104 --> 30:05.673
IO flagged you as blood
when you entered our airspace.

30:07.283 --> 30:08.937
- Okay.

30:09.068 --> 30:12.375
So I had a sister
from a mother I don't know.

30:12.506 --> 30:13.681
[chuckles]

30:13.812 --> 30:15.944
Thanks for telling me.

30:16.075 --> 30:19.382
Do you guys even know
how this works?

30:19.513 --> 30:21.994
- How what works?

30:22.124 --> 30:24.300
- An interrogation.

30:25.736 --> 30:27.477
Do you want me to take over?

30:30.350 --> 30:32.918
"Do you know the victim?"
No.

30:33.048 --> 30:34.963
"Have you ever made contact
with the victim?"

30:35.094 --> 30:36.573
No.

30:36.704 --> 30:39.533
"Did you even know
the victim was alive?"

30:39.663 --> 30:41.752
No.

30:41.883 --> 30:43.929
You guys getting
the hang of this yet?

30:45.974 --> 30:48.281
Do you even know
why she was killed?

30:48.411 --> 30:50.065
- Doesn't matter.

30:50.196 --> 30:51.937
- The case is already solved.

30:53.329 --> 30:56.028
- You know who did it?

30:56.158 --> 30:58.378
- This isn't an interrogation.

30:58.508 --> 31:00.554
We want to help you grieve.

31:02.904 --> 31:04.253
- [laughs]

31:04.384 --> 31:07.300
- A loss must be felt
and properly released.

31:08.736 --> 31:09.998
- This is our job.

31:10.129 --> 31:12.305
- Holy shit.

31:12.435 --> 31:16.265
- When your heart's dark,
your eyes can't see.

31:16.396 --> 31:18.050
We want to help you see again.

31:18.180 --> 31:19.703
You may not have met
your mother,

31:19.834 --> 31:21.227
but you've flown the Moon Loop
hundreds of times.

31:21.357 --> 31:22.402
Doesn't take a detective

31:22.532 --> 31:24.056
to see you wanted
to be near her.

31:25.622 --> 31:28.756
- Is my mother about
to walk through that door?

31:28.887 --> 31:30.671
- She died ten years ago.

31:35.763 --> 31:36.895
- Sorry, daughter.

31:40.768 --> 31:41.769
- You didn't know?

31:43.553 --> 31:45.642
Normally, we would offer
the Bright.

31:45.773 --> 31:47.601
Since you are an outsider,
it is prohibited.

31:47.731 --> 31:50.473
We could do the Scrinjig.
- Ooh.

31:50.604 --> 31:52.475
- We owe you some peace.

31:52.606 --> 31:54.869
- The what?
- Please.

31:55.000 --> 31:57.132
It is our duty to you
and to the dead.

31:57.263 --> 31:58.655
- Mm-hmm.

31:58.786 --> 32:01.397
[tranquil music playing]
- Wait. No.

32:01.528 --> 32:03.095
Stop it. No.

32:03.225 --> 32:04.835
- We must.
- Please.

32:04.966 --> 32:06.750
♪

32:06.881 --> 32:08.839
- How now, detectives?

32:08.970 --> 32:10.015
Feel like a drink?

32:10.145 --> 32:11.494
- Oh, you bet.

32:11.625 --> 32:18.414
♪

32:23.376 --> 32:25.117
[children laughing]

32:25.247 --> 32:27.162
Shouldn't you be
with the Envoy?

32:27.293 --> 32:29.034
- I told her
you needed to be rescued.

32:29.164 --> 32:30.774
- [laughs]

32:30.905 --> 32:33.952
- Those police wouldn't tell me
why they pulled you in.

32:34.082 --> 32:36.606
- Some mix-up
with the manifest.

32:36.737 --> 32:38.826
It's sorted.

32:38.957 --> 32:40.567
- Hmm.

32:40.697 --> 32:42.134
Well, with the First Wave
leaving soon,

32:42.264 --> 32:43.831
everyone's on edge.

32:46.616 --> 32:48.662
Takes a while
to get used to this,

32:48.792 --> 32:50.446
to them.

32:50.577 --> 32:52.709
And I have to warn you,
Mooners don't give up.

32:52.840 --> 32:54.711
You're gonna get that dance
before you go.

32:54.842 --> 32:56.626
- [laughs] Good luck to them.

32:59.020 --> 33:01.980
How is any of this gonna work,
Tomm?

33:02.110 --> 33:04.895
People back home
are killing each other.

33:05.026 --> 33:07.637
They're starving
and wearing gas masks.

33:07.768 --> 33:08.987
- None of this is for them.

33:09.117 --> 33:11.119
It's for their children,

33:11.250 --> 33:12.947
their children's children.

33:14.731 --> 33:16.864
When you're born into it,
it's--

33:16.995 --> 33:18.953
it's not weird,
it's just life.

33:20.737 --> 33:23.044
- On Earth, we fight.

33:23.175 --> 33:24.611
All we know
when the lights go out

33:24.741 --> 33:26.613
is how to survive.

33:26.743 --> 33:29.703
No one learns it.
It's how we're made.

33:31.748 --> 33:33.141
- China Sea.

33:33.272 --> 33:34.664
Two tours.

33:36.231 --> 33:38.233
- Has anyone here ever felt
what that's like?

33:38.364 --> 33:39.539
- No.

33:40.757 --> 33:42.411
They study it.

33:42.542 --> 33:44.022
They study everything.

33:45.240 --> 33:47.677
They know
what we're capable of...

33:47.808 --> 33:49.810
and they guard against it.

33:49.940 --> 33:53.379
- I get that this is
supposed to be our future,

33:53.509 --> 33:56.251
that everything
needs to change,

33:56.382 --> 33:58.732
but you and I know...

33:58.862 --> 34:00.864
darkness finds a way.

34:04.738 --> 34:07.306
[people chanting]

34:07.436 --> 34:09.786
[tranquil music]

34:09.917 --> 34:15.618
♪

34:15.749 --> 34:18.621
[insects buzzing]

34:18.752 --> 34:21.581
[tense music]

34:21.711 --> 34:28.196
♪

34:44.386 --> 34:48.999
♪

34:49.130 --> 34:52.046
[Strego panting]

34:56.746 --> 34:58.357
[device beeps softly]

34:58.487 --> 35:00.446
[whirs]

35:02.274 --> 35:04.580
- [yelps]

35:04.711 --> 35:07.453
[breathing shakily]

35:22.555 --> 35:25.123
[door beeps, whirs]

35:26.733 --> 35:29.779
- Great to see you again,
Detective.

35:29.910 --> 35:32.869
- I don't love the idea
of coming here either.

35:33.000 --> 35:35.263
This is important.

35:35.394 --> 35:38.048
Your sister had a water sister,
Asus.

35:38.179 --> 35:39.311
- A water sister?

35:39.441 --> 35:42.357
- A sister she grew up with.

35:42.488 --> 35:43.793
We don't raise
our own children here.

35:43.924 --> 35:45.665
We raise others' children.

35:45.795 --> 35:47.319
We only see our blood children
when they are born

35:47.449 --> 35:48.581
and when we are about to die.

35:48.711 --> 35:50.757
- Yeah,
we heard all about that.

35:50.887 --> 35:52.976
It's gonna be a tough sell
down there on Earth,

35:53.107 --> 35:54.761
don't you think?

35:54.891 --> 35:56.589
- Well, when you don't
raise your own,

35:56.719 --> 35:58.025
they're all yours.

35:59.505 --> 36:02.160
And we say "up there on Earth."

36:08.078 --> 36:10.124
Asus--
[welding torch buzzing]

36:10.255 --> 36:13.171
Asus has asked for me
to give her the Bright.

36:13.301 --> 36:15.651
This is good because for her,
the pain is deep.

36:15.782 --> 36:16.913
[buzzing continues]

36:17.044 --> 36:18.437
The Bright
will soften her memory.

36:18.567 --> 36:21.483
She's asked to meet you
before she forgets.

36:23.355 --> 36:26.140
- Honestly, I don't care.

36:26.271 --> 36:29.099
I wouldn't have had to deal
with any of this bullshit

36:29.230 --> 36:31.841
if the Envoy's pilot
hadn't gotten sick.

36:31.972 --> 36:34.540
So just tell her I'm sorry.

36:36.846 --> 36:39.109
- She said she has a message.

36:39.240 --> 36:40.807
From your mother.

36:44.289 --> 36:46.508
[dog barking]

36:59.129 --> 37:00.696
- I'm glad you came.

37:02.307 --> 37:03.395
Orbis.

37:04.657 --> 37:05.962
She was Chill's dog.

37:06.093 --> 37:07.921
[Orbis panting]

37:10.228 --> 37:12.317
Tell me how this works.

37:12.447 --> 37:13.753
My first time.

37:15.320 --> 37:18.105
- You take the pill.
Puts you to sleep.

37:18.236 --> 37:21.282
When you wake, you feel better.

37:21.413 --> 37:24.633
The Bright unhooks your heart
from the memories.

37:24.764 --> 37:26.069
The pictures still play,

37:26.200 --> 37:27.984
but there's no friction, no...

37:28.115 --> 37:31.336
- No tear-taste. No chest-dark.

37:31.466 --> 37:33.599
- You'll still remember
your sister,

37:33.729 --> 37:36.471
but the pain will be frozen.

37:36.602 --> 37:38.778
The killing will be gone.

37:38.908 --> 37:42.869
You'll just slide over it
like ice.

37:48.614 --> 37:52.052
- There's pain in your root,
water sister.

37:54.097 --> 37:55.577
I see it.

37:55.708 --> 37:58.885
[somber atmospheric music]

37:59.015 --> 38:01.366
Better for you
to take this than me.

38:01.496 --> 38:08.373
♪

38:10.418 --> 38:11.985
[note chimes]

38:12.115 --> 38:13.291
- Oh.

38:18.078 --> 38:24.954
♪

38:31.091 --> 38:32.658
- I wanted to see your face.

38:34.007 --> 38:35.313
Now I know.

38:36.749 --> 38:38.577
- Now you know what?

38:38.707 --> 38:45.584
♪

38:51.981 --> 38:55.115
- When Chill and I
were little...

38:55.245 --> 38:58.423
we'd play alone
down by the sea.

39:00.555 --> 39:03.906
One day a woman walked
out of the forest.

39:04.037 --> 39:05.691
She had your face.

39:06.953 --> 39:08.389
Before she left,

39:08.520 --> 39:11.827
she picked up Chill
to hold her and say goodbye.

39:13.263 --> 39:15.527
She whispered something
into her ear.

39:20.227 --> 39:22.185
It's cold.

39:22.316 --> 39:24.710
- Mm. That means it's working.

39:24.840 --> 39:29.367
♪

39:29.497 --> 39:31.673
- I don't wanna forget
my sister.

39:31.804 --> 39:34.023
- You'll just forget
the sadness.

39:34.154 --> 39:36.504
- That's where the love is.

39:36.635 --> 39:39.028
- Asus, what did she say?

39:40.334 --> 39:42.249
- Chill told me.

39:42.380 --> 39:44.382
She said she had
another sister.

39:46.558 --> 39:48.560
A sister on the Earth....

39:51.737 --> 39:53.695
Who would watch over her.

39:55.305 --> 39:56.916
Keep her safe.

39:58.700 --> 39:59.919
- She needs to sleep.

40:04.053 --> 40:06.621
- There was a third
in the Glade.

40:06.752 --> 40:08.101
- What?

40:09.885 --> 40:13.062
- There was no third
in the Glade, lady sweet.

40:13.193 --> 40:14.890
I saw the skypictures.

40:16.936 --> 40:18.416
You said you didn't see
the killing.

40:18.546 --> 40:20.548
- I came as she fell.

40:22.463 --> 40:23.943
There were three.

40:25.597 --> 40:27.642
Sister.

40:27.773 --> 40:30.123
Killer.

40:30.253 --> 40:31.777
Watcher.

40:31.907 --> 40:38.784
♪

40:42.222 --> 40:44.659
- There was no third.

40:44.790 --> 40:46.966
- Maybe your machine was wrong.

40:47.096 --> 40:49.621
- IO is never wrong.

40:49.751 --> 40:51.187
- I'd be worried too

40:51.318 --> 40:52.885
if the machine
that makes the air I breathe

40:53.015 --> 40:54.582
and keeps me stuck to this rock

40:54.713 --> 40:56.410
was starting to miss things.

40:56.541 --> 40:58.368
- IO doesn't miss anything.

40:58.499 --> 41:00.153
When a life is taken,
it sees everything.

41:00.283 --> 41:01.459
- How?

41:01.589 --> 41:03.373
How does it see?

41:03.504 --> 41:05.158
- The satellites.

41:05.288 --> 41:07.900
From birth, we're all marked.
See?

41:08.030 --> 41:09.205
- An implant.

41:09.336 --> 41:11.207
IO tracks you?

41:11.338 --> 41:15.385
- We read Orwell and Kazuo,
Mwangi.

41:15.516 --> 41:18.214
IO doesn't watch us
to control us.

41:18.345 --> 41:20.739
It watches us to learn from us.

41:20.869 --> 41:23.437
Our successes, our mistakes.
We all contribute.

41:23.568 --> 41:25.657
[horn blares in distance]

41:25.787 --> 41:27.659
The Envoy's speech
will begin soon.

41:31.271 --> 41:33.055
- For thousands of years,

41:33.186 --> 41:36.406
agriculture forced us
to enslave each other.

41:36.537 --> 41:39.540
Energy demand created
massive inequality.

41:39.671 --> 41:41.934
Scarcity divided us.

41:42.064 --> 41:44.284
Pestilence and disease
weakened us.

41:44.414 --> 41:46.286
But over the last century,

41:46.416 --> 41:49.028
we have turned a corner.

41:49.158 --> 41:51.160
With the assistance of IO,

41:51.291 --> 41:53.815
we are on the verge
of being able to explore

41:53.946 --> 41:56.296
an undiscovered country.

41:56.426 --> 42:00.343
An Earth population
with all its basic needs met

42:00.474 --> 42:03.303
with a climate that no longer
seeks to destroy us.

42:03.433 --> 42:05.392
So how do we now transition

42:05.523 --> 42:08.830
to our own better future
with IO?

42:08.961 --> 42:10.876
The mission of Moonhaven

42:11.006 --> 42:14.532
is to show us on Earth
the way.

42:14.662 --> 42:17.317
Very soon, the cultural
and technological leaps

42:17.447 --> 42:19.537
that are working here on Lune

42:19.667 --> 42:21.843
will be brought back
to the Mother.

42:21.974 --> 42:25.238
As we enter this new phase
and commence the Bridge,

42:25.368 --> 42:30.199
we will not forget the trust
you have placed in all of us.

42:30.330 --> 42:32.811
The future is better.

42:32.941 --> 42:35.814
[tranquil music]

42:35.944 --> 42:39.905
♪

42:43.996 --> 42:45.563
[bird caws]

42:54.441 --> 42:56.399
- Can you at least admit
something is off

42:56.530 --> 42:58.053
about this case?

42:59.489 --> 43:02.275
- Yes.
- You can?

43:02.405 --> 43:03.755
- Yeah, I can feel it here.

43:05.583 --> 43:07.541
- It doesn't matter
what you feel.

43:07.672 --> 43:10.500
You need to think.

43:10.631 --> 43:14.069
Who was Chill Spen?
Why was she killed?

43:14.200 --> 43:17.725
- I know who Chill Spen was--
your blood sister.

43:17.856 --> 43:20.467
You are connected
to this place, this person.

43:20.598 --> 43:21.599
- Shh.

43:24.906 --> 43:26.865
[dog barking]

43:26.995 --> 43:29.694
[tense music]

43:29.824 --> 43:36.396
♪

43:46.058 --> 43:50.018
♪

43:50.149 --> 43:51.977
- Stop!

43:52.107 --> 43:53.979
There's no going past this.

43:54.109 --> 43:55.458
- They did.

43:56.808 --> 43:58.897
- Stop!

43:59.027 --> 44:00.507
Please!

44:00.638 --> 44:02.248
Bella!

44:04.380 --> 44:06.208
- [breathing heavily]

44:06.339 --> 44:09.168
[muffled barking]

44:09.298 --> 44:16.175
♪

44:32.539 --> 44:35.368
[Orbis barking]

44:35.498 --> 44:41.461
♪

44:41.591 --> 44:44.464
[breathing heavily]

44:57.912 --> 44:59.958
[Orbis whimpering]

45:00.088 --> 45:06.878
♪

45:18.367 --> 45:20.326
- We welcome the Envoy of IO.

45:20.456 --> 45:23.329
You speech to the Earth Mother
was...

45:23.459 --> 45:25.635
[sighs] Excellent.

45:25.766 --> 45:27.246
We owe you all.

45:38.431 --> 45:40.128
Speak, do.

45:40.259 --> 45:42.304
- You know why I've come.

45:42.435 --> 45:45.220
ICON has requested
the council swap.

45:48.049 --> 45:52.575
- Our council has
two more years.

45:52.706 --> 45:54.621
- New members will be
chosen immediately

45:54.752 --> 45:57.276
and then elect
a new council chair.

46:00.714 --> 46:04.283
- The First Wave is brinked
to leave for Earth.

46:04.413 --> 46:07.025
I've spent my life
preparing for this day.

46:07.155 --> 46:10.768
- IO has detected
a pattern of responses

46:10.898 --> 46:13.945
which suggests a risk
of corruption of workflow

46:14.075 --> 46:16.599
if things remain unchanged.

46:16.730 --> 46:18.384
- I am not trusted?

46:18.514 --> 46:21.256
- IO doesn't trust or distrust.

46:21.387 --> 46:26.131
You know IO is fluent
in the history of our mistakes.

46:26.261 --> 46:30.700
It has analyzed past actions
to predict future behavior.

46:30.831 --> 46:33.660
- IO sees the future
and the past.

46:35.618 --> 46:37.795
But history doesn't always
repeat.

46:39.318 --> 46:42.582
- It's a pretty safe bet
with our kind.

46:42.712 --> 46:45.063
That's not an accusation.

46:45.193 --> 46:47.152
As far as I'm aware,
you've done nothing wrong,

46:47.282 --> 46:48.936
Council Maite.

46:49.067 --> 46:51.156
The swap is preventative.

46:51.286 --> 46:53.506
You can step aside with honor.

46:59.338 --> 47:01.775
- Know what I speak of?

47:01.906 --> 47:02.994
The Pivot?

47:07.955 --> 47:10.871
The movement from a people
who seek to understand

47:11.002 --> 47:14.962
mysteries of the universe
to one that creates them.

47:16.659 --> 47:20.315
Do you believe in God,
Indira Mare?

47:22.317 --> 47:25.277
- I believe
in right and wrong.

47:25.407 --> 47:27.540
If knowing the difference
comes from somewhere beyond,

47:27.670 --> 47:29.411
so be it.

47:29.542 --> 47:32.675
- Sometimes everything changes.

47:32.806 --> 47:36.592
With thunder or a pin drop,

47:36.723 --> 47:39.857
we pivot by a grace
bigger-better than IO.

47:41.597 --> 47:43.773
Could the machine
see that coming?

47:43.904 --> 47:46.428
[tense music]

47:46.559 --> 47:47.777
- I'll expect
your full cooperation

47:47.908 --> 47:49.257
with the swap.

47:49.388 --> 47:51.564
Thank you for your time,
Council Maite.

47:51.694 --> 47:53.000
This has been
a productive trip.

47:53.131 --> 47:54.262
I hope you'll agree.

47:54.393 --> 48:00.138
♪

48:00.268 --> 48:01.879
It's time to go.

48:02.009 --> 48:03.619
Get us clearance to leave,
and I'll meet you at the ship.

48:03.750 --> 48:10.670
♪

48:12.237 --> 48:15.109
[bright melody chiming]

48:15.240 --> 48:21.072
♪

48:27.469 --> 48:30.255
[muffled chatter]

48:44.356 --> 48:47.098
[people chattering]

48:50.840 --> 48:52.930
- Oh, Bella.

48:53.060 --> 48:55.367
This is Lone, my love,

48:55.497 --> 48:56.890
and my children.

48:59.806 --> 49:00.850
Are you hungry?

49:00.981 --> 49:02.026
- Yeah.

49:02.156 --> 49:04.637
[device whirs]

49:04.767 --> 49:07.509
[lively traditional music]

49:07.640 --> 49:11.600
♪

49:11.731 --> 49:13.211
- When they got out there,

49:13.341 --> 49:16.518
they found you barely alive
under a dead tree.

49:16.649 --> 49:19.260
I suggested they bring you here
to recover.

49:19.391 --> 49:21.219
- Thank you.

49:21.349 --> 49:22.829
- [whispering]
She's strange.

49:24.439 --> 49:26.441
- Well, you're lucky
to be alive.

49:32.578 --> 49:34.362
- Our son, Wish,

49:34.493 --> 49:37.322
will ride the First Wave
back to Earth.

49:37.452 --> 49:39.977
The young and the strong
go first.

49:40.107 --> 49:41.456
- You'll be the tip
of the spear.

49:43.676 --> 49:45.373
- You make it sound
like an attack.

49:45.504 --> 49:47.549
- It's an old expression.

49:47.680 --> 49:49.073
- Do Earthers understand

49:49.203 --> 49:50.813
that we're coming
to help them begin again?

49:50.944 --> 49:53.338
- Earthers understand
you have the tech

49:53.468 --> 49:56.036
that will let them
eat and breathe.

49:56.167 --> 49:58.299
It might take some time
for us to pick up on the nuance

49:58.430 --> 49:59.692
of everything else.

49:59.822 --> 50:01.737
- The power
to fix all your problems

50:01.868 --> 50:04.436
will destroy you without
a culture to contain it.

50:04.566 --> 50:07.004
- Their problems
are our problem.

50:08.483 --> 50:11.095
We come from the Mother,
and we shall return.

50:11.225 --> 50:13.314
- You were stupid
to go past the wall.

50:13.445 --> 50:16.839
Someone who was born here
would never make that choice.

50:16.970 --> 50:18.537
- I told them what happened.

50:18.667 --> 50:20.104
The dog was crazed
by an animal,

50:20.234 --> 50:22.802
and you were brave enough
to go in after them.

50:22.932 --> 50:25.761
She's safe and at home now.

50:25.892 --> 50:28.286
- Earthers see the world
like children do--

50:28.416 --> 50:30.897
full of rules
to be followed or broken.

50:31.028 --> 50:33.291
A Mooner is taught
to see truths

50:33.421 --> 50:35.467
and lives by them.

50:35.597 --> 50:37.338
- Yes, Fritz.

50:39.949 --> 50:41.168
- Thanks, Fritz.

50:43.214 --> 50:45.999
- Well, I'd pretty much break
any rule

50:46.130 --> 50:48.828
to save a cute dog's life.

50:48.958 --> 50:50.612
Just the cute ones, though.

50:50.743 --> 50:53.006
If they're not cute,
I say let 'em asphyxiate.

50:56.923 --> 50:59.056
These triangles...

50:59.186 --> 51:00.622
are delicious.

51:00.753 --> 51:01.928
- [laughs]

51:06.150 --> 51:08.935
[crickets chirping]

51:15.724 --> 51:18.553
- The Envoy's business
is finished.

51:18.684 --> 51:20.381
I need to get back to CAT.

51:22.166 --> 51:24.733
- Thank you for only telling
part of the story.

51:24.864 --> 51:27.432
- You saw her too? The girl.

51:27.562 --> 51:28.998
- I was far behind.

51:29.129 --> 51:30.435
Found you alone.

51:32.698 --> 51:34.352
- I'm not sure what I saw.

51:36.789 --> 51:38.443
- Little ghost?

51:38.573 --> 51:40.053
- [exhales]

51:40.184 --> 51:41.750
- There will be a reason.

51:41.881 --> 51:44.057
There's always a reason.

51:44.188 --> 51:47.539
But Fritz would be terrified
of what he can't explain.

51:47.669 --> 51:50.672
- He barely said anything
and I hated him.

51:50.803 --> 51:51.847
[both chuckle]

51:51.978 --> 51:53.414
Who is he?

51:57.723 --> 51:59.768
It's complicated.

51:59.899 --> 52:02.293
- It's--it's simple.

52:07.167 --> 52:08.777
I wish you didn't
have to leave.

52:08.908 --> 52:10.779
I'm a bad detective.

52:10.910 --> 52:12.694
- You are.
[chuckles]

52:12.825 --> 52:16.045
Don't trust everything, Paul.

52:16.176 --> 52:17.482
Use your head.

52:22.095 --> 52:24.619
- I will not fear the darkness.

52:24.750 --> 52:26.665
- Because you are the light.

52:30.669 --> 52:31.800
[chuckles]

52:33.628 --> 52:36.022
I gotta go. My stuff's inside.

52:44.552 --> 52:45.858
I'm sorry.

52:47.381 --> 52:48.991
Is this your room?

52:50.863 --> 52:53.692
I like your Earth.

52:53.822 --> 52:56.042
She's beautiful from far away.

52:57.609 --> 52:59.306
- You're going back?

52:59.437 --> 53:00.829
- It's home.

53:02.396 --> 53:04.006
- He told me your blood mother
was a Mooner,

53:04.137 --> 53:05.530
and your sister too.

53:05.660 --> 53:08.750
- Yeah, but I never knew 'em.

53:08.881 --> 53:10.796
- I never met my mada either,

53:10.926 --> 53:13.277
but I see her every day
in my thinks.

53:16.802 --> 53:18.630
[melody chimes]

53:18.760 --> 53:19.848
[tranquil music playing]
You need the dance.

53:19.979 --> 53:21.937
- Elna, no.

53:22.068 --> 53:23.939
- Please.
- Mm-mm.

53:24.070 --> 53:26.028
- It's for you.

53:26.159 --> 53:27.769
To remember.

53:27.900 --> 53:34.820
♪

54:04.241 --> 54:11.117
♪

55:06.825 --> 55:09.218
[Peggy Lee's
"Me and My Shadow" playing]

55:09.349 --> 55:10.829
- ♪ Me

55:10.959 --> 55:13.571
♪

55:13.701 --> 55:14.876
♪ And my

55:15.007 --> 55:16.965
♪

55:17.096 --> 55:19.533
♪ Shadow

55:19.664 --> 55:21.274
♪

55:21.405 --> 55:23.494
♪ Not a soul

55:23.624 --> 55:27.062
♪ To tell my troubles to

55:27.193 --> 55:29.064
♪

55:29.195 --> 55:33.678
♪ And when it's 12:00

55:33.808 --> 55:36.420
♪

55:36.550 --> 55:39.248
♪ We climb the stairs
[alarm chiming]

55:39.379 --> 55:41.860
♪

55:41.990 --> 55:44.079
♪ We never knock

55:44.210 --> 55:46.125
[tense music]

55:46.255 --> 55:48.606
♪ Because
there's nobody there ♪

55:48.736 --> 55:50.216
♪

55:50.347 --> 55:51.913
♪ Just me

55:52.044 --> 55:54.786
[alarm continues]

55:54.916 --> 55:56.701
♪ And my

55:56.831 --> 55:58.180
♪

55:58.311 --> 56:00.705
♪ Shadow

56:00.835 --> 56:06.754
♪

56:06.885 --> 56:09.714
[electricity buzzing]

56:19.376 --> 56:21.378
[electricity crackles]
- [screams]

56:23.858 --> 56:26.295
[grunts, groans]

56:26.426 --> 56:27.688
- Who are you?

56:27.819 --> 56:28.907
- [panting] I'm no one.

56:30.996 --> 56:33.738
I'm nothing now.
[panting]

56:33.868 --> 56:37.002
- Spare me your Moon poetry
and tell me why you're here.

56:38.743 --> 56:40.397
- R-ride to the Mother.

56:41.746 --> 56:43.269
Wanna leave here forever.

56:44.575 --> 56:47.012
Don't deserve to be here.

56:47.142 --> 56:49.928
Done deep wounds to the place
and its people.

56:51.712 --> 56:53.758
Just take me, please.

56:53.888 --> 56:55.368
- You.

56:55.499 --> 56:57.414
You murdered my sister?

56:58.589 --> 56:59.894
- Sister?

57:03.332 --> 57:05.291
She called and you answered.

57:05.422 --> 57:07.119
- What?
[door whirs]

57:07.249 --> 57:08.947
- Bella?

57:19.784 --> 57:22.439
- Stay down here
and shut the hell up.

57:22.569 --> 57:24.005
[Elvis Presley's
"Suspicious Minds" playing]

57:24.136 --> 57:26.443
- ♪ So if an old friend
I know ♪

57:26.573 --> 57:28.793
♪ Stops by to say hello

57:28.923 --> 57:31.099
♪

57:31.230 --> 57:35.539
♪ Would I still see suspicion
in your eyes? ♪

57:35.669 --> 57:36.931
- There you are.

57:38.150 --> 57:39.760
Indira's on her way back.

57:39.891 --> 57:41.936
- ♪ Here we go again

57:42.067 --> 57:43.372
- Are you all right? ♪

57:43.503 --> 57:45.418
- Yeah.

57:45.549 --> 57:47.072
- Excited to get back
to terra firma?

57:47.202 --> 57:48.682
- [laughs]
I'll take liftoff.

57:48.813 --> 57:50.945
Gravity's a drag, as they say.

57:52.251 --> 57:54.688
- ♪ Yes, I'm crying

57:54.819 --> 57:56.821
- Is there anywhere
you feel at home, Bella?

57:56.951 --> 57:59.084
- ♪ We can't go on together

57:59.214 --> 58:02.043
- Mm, Mooners call that
"wanderflect."

58:02.174 --> 58:05.438
Without an identity
or community, we float,

58:05.569 --> 58:07.266
reflecting that of others.

58:07.396 --> 58:08.833
- Tomm.
- Yes.

58:08.963 --> 58:10.704
- [laughs]
Stop teaching me.

58:10.835 --> 58:13.838
♪

58:13.968 --> 58:16.710
- ♪ Oh, let our love survive

58:16.841 --> 58:18.495
- Why did you come up?

58:18.625 --> 58:20.018
- It's done.

58:20.148 --> 58:24.413
♪

58:24.544 --> 58:28.113
Where one world ends,
the next one begins.

58:30.594 --> 58:32.204
[gun blasts]

58:32.334 --> 58:33.379
[thud]

58:34.902 --> 58:37.035
- ♪ Mm

58:37.165 --> 58:38.689
♪

58:38.819 --> 58:40.604
- [grunts]
- [gasps]

58:40.734 --> 58:42.562
- I really wish
you wouldn't've seen that.

58:42.693 --> 58:44.390
- ♪ We're caught in a trap

58:44.521 --> 58:46.261
[electricity crackles]
- [grunts]

58:46.392 --> 58:48.133
- ♪ I can't walk out

58:48.263 --> 58:50.135
- [gasping]

58:50.265 --> 58:54.139
- ♪ Because I love you
too much, baby ♪

58:54.269 --> 58:57.055
- [groaning in pain]

58:58.752 --> 59:00.232
- ♪ Why can't you see

59:00.362 --> 59:02.103
♪

59:02.234 --> 59:04.976
♪ What you're doin' to me

59:05.106 --> 59:06.412
- [grunts]

59:06.543 --> 59:08.196
- Ahh!

59:08.327 --> 59:10.155
- ♪ When you don't believe
a word I say ♪

59:10.285 --> 59:11.417
- [grunts]

59:11.548 --> 59:12.853
♪

59:12.984 --> 59:14.812
♪ Don't you know I'm

59:14.942 --> 59:16.596
♪ Caught in a trap?
[both grunt]

59:16.727 --> 59:18.598
♪

59:18.729 --> 59:20.469
♪ I can't walk out

59:20.600 --> 59:21.819
♪

59:21.949 --> 59:23.472
- [shouts, chokes]

59:23.603 --> 59:26.911
- ♪ Because I love you
too much, baby ♪

59:27.041 --> 59:28.695
♪

59:28.826 --> 59:30.828
- [groans]

59:30.958 --> 59:32.830
- ♪ Caught in a trap

59:32.960 --> 59:34.701
- [growls]

59:34.832 --> 59:36.137
- ♪ I can't walk out

59:36.268 --> 59:39.184
- [grunts in pain]

59:39.314 --> 59:42.448
- ♪ Because I love you
too much, baby ♪

59:42.579 --> 59:44.581
♪

59:44.711 --> 59:47.018
- [grunts]
[device whirs]

59:47.148 --> 59:49.281
[tense music]

59:49.411 --> 59:50.499
♪

59:50.630 --> 59:52.284
- [gasps, coughs]

59:55.461 --> 59:58.856
- [moans in pain]

59:58.986 --> 1:00:05.906
♪

1:00:12.870 --> 1:00:14.436
[door whirs]

1:00:14.567 --> 1:00:17.396
- [breathing heavily]

1:00:22.749 --> 1:00:24.577
- I had a bad feeling.

1:00:24.708 --> 1:00:26.187
- I walked into something.

1:00:26.318 --> 1:00:28.189
[dark music]

1:00:28.320 --> 1:00:32.019
I...I don't know who to trust.

1:00:32.150 --> 1:00:36.763
♪

1:00:36.894 --> 1:00:38.373
- Trust me.

1:00:38.504 --> 1:00:45.467
♪

1:00:52.431 --> 1:00:54.607
[dramatic music]

1:00:54.738 --> 1:00:58.742
- You have to believe
in something, Bella Sway.

1:00:58.872 --> 1:01:02.093
- ICON is concerned
some Earth extremists

1:01:02.223 --> 1:01:04.878
have found a way
to get an agent on the Moon.

1:01:05.009 --> 1:01:08.447
- Could this all be connected
to the death of Chill Spen?

1:01:08.577 --> 1:01:11.363
- You will step down.
- And if I don't?

1:01:11.493 --> 1:01:13.321
- You would
destabilize everything

1:01:13.452 --> 1:01:14.888
just to stay in power.

1:01:15.019 --> 1:01:16.194
♪

1:01:16.324 --> 1:01:18.413
- Moonhaven isn't a people.

1:01:18.544 --> 1:01:20.633
It's a purpose.

1:01:20.764 --> 1:01:22.287
- [grunting]

1:01:22.417 --> 1:01:24.376
I'm transformed
because of what you did to me.

1:01:24.506 --> 1:01:26.291
♪

1:01:26.421 --> 1:01:28.597
- She's not what
she seems to be.

1:01:28.728 --> 1:01:30.991
♪

1:01:31.122 --> 1:01:33.254
- You're making a mistake.

1:01:33.385 --> 1:01:34.952
- What is this?

1:01:35.082 --> 1:01:36.431
- It's a trap!

1:01:36.562 --> 1:01:39.391
The Earthers will
kill us all when we land!

1:01:39.521 --> 1:01:40.697
♪

1:01:40.827 --> 1:01:42.786
- If we cannot
heal the dark heart

1:01:42.916 --> 1:01:44.178
of Bella Sway,

1:01:44.309 --> 1:01:47.094
how can we ever hope
to succeed?

1:01:47.225 --> 1:01:49.401
- This is not the end.

1:01:49.531 --> 1:01:52.056
♪

1:01:52.186 --> 1:01:54.232
- No!

1:01:55.668 --> 1:01:57.801
- This is the beginning.

